article.description: Jordan Heading had a season-high 28 points as California Baptist defeated Cal State Bakersfield 72-58 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Heading leads California Baptist over CSU Bakersfield 72-58
article.linkText: Heading leads California Baptist over CSU Bakersfield 72-58
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Jordan Heading had a season-high 28 points as California Baptist defeated Cal State Bakersfield 72-58 on Saturday night. Heading shot 6 for 8 on 3-pointers. Milan Acquaah had 11 points and eight assists for California Baptist (15-11, 6-6 Western Athletic Conference). Ty Rowell added 11 points. De'jon Davis had 12 rebounds for the visitors. Jarkel Joiner had 22 points for the Roadrunners (16-11, 7-6). Rickey Holden added 10 points. Damiyne Durham had 10 points. The Lancers evened the season series against the Roadrunners with the win. Cal State Bakersfield defeated California Baptist 88-84 on Jan. 24. California Baptist takes on Seattle at home on Thursday. Cal State Bakersfield plays Grand Canyon on the road next Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap , using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
